    <max_step_size>.001</max_step_size>
    <real_time_factor>1.0</real_time_factor>
</physics>
The physics tag specifies the type and properties FOR THE PHYSICS ENGINE(this is FOR GAZEBO!!)
You get to choose the type of physics library to implement with options such as Ode, Bullet, Simbody and Dart etc.
For now we leave as ignored

As for the 
    -<max_step_size>: this is for the accuracy of calculations, the smaller it is the better the results BUT needs more computational power! 
    -<real_time_factor>: the ration of simulation time to real time....so maybe in this case this is known as 1s maybe.....
