the build system inside it to do the hardwork for us....we are going to need the .sdf that contains the object in question in this case we're going to do a:
    -1.coke can .sdf file
    -2.python file that runs the ROS2 code
    -3.a yaml file for the topics for ROS2 and gazebo

the arguement would go a little something like this.....
ros2 launch ros_gz_sim gz_sim.launch.py gz_args:=empty.sdf
now replace "gz_sim.lanuch.py" with a custom python file you have made for yourself

